<TITLE> Bangladesh, Switzerland sign deal to avoid double taxation </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 10 (bdnews24.com)  Bangladesh and Switzerland Monday signed an agreement to avoid double taxation. Updates with changes Swiss ambassador in Dhaka Dora Rapold and chairman of National Board of Revenue (NBR) Muhammad Abdul Majid signed the agreement at the conference room of the NBR. "The treaty is expected to contribute to favourable conditions for Swiss investments in Bangladesh," said a press statement issued by the Swiss embassy in Dhaka. Swiss companies in Bangladesh since independence have invested in such sectors as pharmaceuticals, food and diary and cement. Switzerland has 26 investment projects in Bangladesh with a volume of $118 million, according to the embassy. Companies having invested in Bangladesh include Nestle, Novartis, Holcim and Syngenta. Around 100 Swiss companies or their representatives have presence in the country. In 2006, Bangladesh export to Switzerland was $ 118 million and Swiss export to Bangladesh was $107 million, according to official Swiss figures. The 32 member 'Switzerland-Bangladesh Business Forum' (SBBF) was formed in Dhaka in 2004 to facilitate trade and investment cooperation between the two countries. bdn
